I"‘<h2 id="design-documents">Design Documents</h2>

<p>In the second phase of the Documenting the Now project we started writing up
brief design documents that help us organize our work at a level of granularity
somewhere between the global <a href="https://github.com/docnow/roadmap#readme">Project Roadmap</a> and what is provided by task
management tools like GitHub, Trello and Asana during our sprints. The idea is
for these documents to pitch and socialize a broad area of work before diving
into the nuts and bolts of the work. They also serve as a record of the work we
have focused on, and help us see how our ideas may have changed over time.</p>

<p>Please feel free to ask questions in the <a href="https://github.com/docnow/docnow.github.io/issues">Issue Tracker</a> for this website, in
<a href="https://bit.ly/docnow-slack">Slack</a>, or to drop us an email at info@docnow.io.</p>

